display="inline"><![CDATA[a\colon  X_\bullet \to  S]]></fr:tex> be an augmented simplicial topological space.
    For every sheaf <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, we have a morphism
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \varphi \colon  F       \to  a_*a^*F     ]]></fr:tex>
    from the adjunction <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a^*\dashv  a_*]]></fr:tex>.
    This morphism derives to a morphism of functors from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(S)]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(S)]]></fr:tex>, namely

    <fr:tree
