display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> is of <fr:em>cohomological descent</fr:em> if, for every abelian sheaf <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, we have
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       F\xrightarrow {\sim }\operatorname {Ker}({a_0}_*{a_0}^*F\to {a_1}_*{a_1}^*F)     ]]></fr:tex>
    and
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \mathrm {R}^i a_*a^*F       = 0       \quad \text {for }i>0.     ]]></fr:tex></fr:p><fr:p>This is equivalent to asking that <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.1.1"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.1.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.3.1.1" /> be an isomorphism.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
