display="inline"><![CDATA[k=\infty ]]></fr:tex>, (IV) of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5.xml"
number="5.3.5" /> implies that the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\colon  X_\bullet \to  S]]></fr:tex> are of cohomological descent if the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\varphi _n)_{n+1}]]></fr:tex> are of universal cohomological descent.
    For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-1,0]]></fr:tex>, these maps are
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       (\varphi _n)_{n+1}       =       \begin {cases}         X_0\xrightarrow {a}S         &\text {if }n=-1       \\X_1\xrightarrow {(\delta _0,\delta _1)}X_0\times _S X_0         &\text {if }n=0.       \end {cases}     ]]></fr:tex>
    
    For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=1]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\operatorname {cosq}\operatorname {sq}_1(X_\bullet ))_1]]></fr:tex> is the subspace of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_1\times _S X_1\times _S X_1]]></fr:tex> consisting of the triples <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(x,y,z)]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _0x=\delta _0y]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _1x=\delta _0z]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _1y=\delta _1z]]></fr:tex>.
    The map <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\varphi _1)_2]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\mapsto (\delta _0x,\delta _1x,\delta _2x)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k=0]]></fr:tex>, (IV) of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.5.xml"
number="5.3.5" /> is <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.4"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.4.xml"
taxon="Definition"
number="5.3.4" />.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
