display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {U}=(U_i)_{i\in  I}]]></fr:tex> be an open cover, or a finite locally closed cover, of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
    Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X=\coprod _{i\in  I}U_i]]></fr:tex>.
    Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\colon  X\to  S]]></fr:tex> is of cohomological descent.
    The spectral sequence in <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.3.2"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.3.3.2.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.3.3.2" /> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_\bullet =\operatorname {cosq}(X\to  S)]]></fr:tex> is then exactly the Leray spectral sequence of the cover <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {U}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
